yocardial infarction"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary therapeutic indication for isosorbide mononitrate is \u003Cstrong\u003Eprevention of angina\u003C/strong\u003E. It reduces cardiac workload through venous and arterial vasodilation, improving the balance between myocardial oxygen supply and demand.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect, and explained below:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of heart failure\u003C/strong\u003E: while nitrates can provide symptomatic relief in acute heart failure, this is not the primary indication for long-acting preparations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EManagement of hypertension\u003C/strong\u003E: although nitrates have blood pressure lowering effects, other antihypertensive medications have more favourable properties for long-term BP control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevention of arrhythmias\u003C/strong\u003E: nitrates do not possess direct antiarrhythmic properties and therefore are not indicated for rhythm control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of myocardial infarction\u003C/strong\u003E: while nitrates may be used during acute coronary syndromes for symptom relief, this is not their main indication.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELong-acting nitrates like isosorbide mononitrate are particularly useful for preventing predictable angina attacks, such as those triggered by exercise or stress.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Isosorbide mononitrate is primarily used to prevent and treat angina by reducing cardiac workload.","Nitrates improve the oxygen supply-demand balance in the heart through vasodilation.","Prevention of angina attacks is the main therapeutic indication for long-acting nitrates."]